/*E*/
/*S*/ Kurzbeschreibung
@NODE "Kurz-Beschreibung" "FreshIcons-Documentation / Short-Overview"
@{bpen 4}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{b}1. Short-Overview@{ub}@{FG TEXT}@{bpen 0}

@{par}@{FG FILL}@{b}@{apen 11}FreshIcons is a collection of icons with the following features:@{apen 1}@{ub}@{FG TEXT}

@{par}· Freeware
@{par}· @{b}16@{ub} Colors (really colorful)
@{par}· MagicWB-compatible
@{par}· Some useful Icon-Tools included
@{par}· about @{b}500@{ub} Icons with Fresh-Design
@{par}· about @{b}100@{ub} DockBrushes for the ToolManager by Stefan Becker
@{par}· about @{b}360@{ub} Symbols for creating your own Fresh-styled icons.
@{par}· An ENV-Variable is supported for recognizing whether the FreshColors are active or not

@ENDNODE
/*E*/
/*S*/ Wichtig
@node "Wichtig" "FreshIcons-Documentation / Important"
@{bpen 4}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{b}2. Important!@{ub}@{FG TEXT}@{bpen 0}

@{par}To admire the FreshIcons in they full beauty, it's necessary to set up
your Workbench with 16 colors. It's the best to do this by using the
@{"ScreenMode-Preferences program" SYSTEM "SYS:Prefs/ScreenMode"} of the AmigaOS.

@{par}If the colors of your Workbench do not match with the colors in the
preview-picture after the installation and a reset (what is really
improbably or the entry in your user-startup was skipped while installa-
tion, then start @{"FreshFarben16" SYSTEM "/Tools/FreshFarben16"} out of the FreshIcons/Tools directory which
simply sets temporarly the first 16 colors of your WB. Now the colors
should be right.

@{par}If you have problems with FreshIcons, you can try to fix them with the help
of this @{"problem-solve-list." LINK "ProblemSolve.Guide/main"}

@{par}@{"PreView-Picture" SYSTEM "Sys:Utilities/MultiView /PreView.iff screen"} Click here to display a preview-picture of FreshIcons.

@endnode
/*E*/
/*S*/ Einleitung
@NODE "Einleitung" "FreshIcons-Documentation / Introduction"
@{bpen 4}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{b}3. Introduction@{ub}@{FG TEXT}@{bpen 0}

@{par}We all know the icons of the Workbench with 4 colors. Not necessary nice
and because they are drawn for a HiRes-screenmode they look compressed on
screens with 1:1 pixel-aspect ratio (especially on graphic boards)

@{par}The most of you (if not everybody), also know the very beautyful 8-Color
icons of the MagicWB-Packet by Martin Huttenloher. These icons really look
much better, are very detailful and not so flat Workbenches with a higher
resolution, which should be standard today.

@{par}And then there are people for them it ain't enough.
I'm such a guy.

@{par}To me the icons weren't colored enough so i decided to draw this collection
of 16-color icons.

@{par}@{apen 13}PS:@{apen 1} The pattern of MagicWB also look fantastic with FreshIcons.

@ENDNODE
/*E*/
/*S*/ Features
@NODE "Eigenschaften" "FreshIcons-Documentation / Features"
@{bpen 4}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{b}4. Features of FreshIcons@{ub}@{FG TEXT}@{bpen 0}

@{par}@{FG FILL}@{i}@{apen 11}System@{ui}@{FG TEXT}

@{par}· While the installation of  FreshIcons  a  programm  is  installed
@{par}  which  will  be started in your user-startup. This program called
@{par}  LockFreshPens is  for  setting  the  right  FreshColors  on  your
@{par}  Workbench.  If  every  color could be set, it sets a ENV-Variable
@{par}  "PALETTESET" containing  the  Value  "FRESH".  If  this  Variable
@{par}  contains  this  value  your program can assume this palette to be
@{par}  present. In the developer-directory of the FreshIcons-package are
@{par}  sourcefiles in C and ARexx on how to determine whether the Fresh-
@{par}  Palette is active.
@{par}  See also the info-window of "FI" or "CAFIC".

@{par}@{FG FILL}@{i}@{apen 11}Palette: @{ui}@{FG TEXT}
->@{bpen 0} @{bpen 1} @{bpen 2} @{bpen 3} @{bpen 4} @{bpen 5} @{bpen 6} @{bpen 7} @{bpen 8} @{bpen 9} @{bpen 10} @{bpen 11} @{bpen 12} @{bpen 13} @{bpen 14} @{bpen 15} @{bpen 0}<-

@{par}· Every needed color is contained in the  FreshPalette  or  can  be
@{par}  mixed  to  provide  a  palette which can be used for almost every
@{par}  purposes.

@{par}· The 4 Default-Colors of the Workbench a part of the  FreshPalette
@{par}  to be compatible to the defaulticons.

@{par}· The further 4 colors are  these  of  the  MagicWB-Package.  These
@{par}  colors are choosen very good and can be used very flexible. To be
@{par}  compatible to these icons and the patterns of  MagicWB  they  are
@{par}  part of the FreshPalette.

@{par}@{FG FILL}@{i}@{apen 11}Design@{ui}@{FG TEXT}

@{par}· All FreshIcons in this Packet have the same Size of 58x38 Pixels.
@{par}  Through that is possible to position the icons in uniform manner.

@{par}· Drawer-, Tool- and Projecticons have all a uniform basedesign to
@{par}  recognize in an easy way which icon you have to do with.

@{par}@{FG FILL}@{i}@{apen 11}Software-Set-Installations@{ui}@{FG TEXT}

@{par}· This  Package contains  installer-skripts  for the  icons of  the
@{par}  workbench  and for the  default-icons.  Due to keep  the  archive
@{par}  small we didn't put  more  in. Later,  other  skripts in seperate
@{CODE}@{par}  archives will follow.

@endnode
/*E*/
/*S*/ Inhalt
@NODE "Inhalt" "FreshIcons-Documentation / Contents"
@{bpen 4}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{b}5. Contents@{ub}@{FG TEXT}@{bpen 0}

@{apen 11}@{par}This packet contains more than 500 icons. So far:@{apen 1}

@{par}· all icons of the Default-Workbench
@{par}· some different drive-icons
@{par}· many different drawer-icons
@{par}· many different project-icons
@{par}· many different tools-icons
@{par}· some prefs-icons for diverse well known PD-Tools
@{par}· some tool-icons for some well known PD-Tools
@{par}· some icons for well known commercial Programs
@{par}· all necessary default-icons
@{par}· and all necessary templates

@{par}And then there are also more than 130 dock brushes for the Toolmanager by
Stefan Becker, as 3 IFF-ILBM-pictures, with all together 360 different
symbols. Feel free to use them for creating your own icons.

@{par}And last but not least, there is a drawer containing some useful tools
which shall help you to install the FreshIcons on your Amiga. These tools
were written by Christian Taulien especially for this Iconpackage.

@ENDNODE
/*E*/
/*S*/ Requirements
@NODE "Voraussetzungen" "FreshIcons-Documentation / Requirements"
@NEXT Danksagungen
@{bpen 4}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{b}6. Requirements for using the FreshIcons.@{ub}@{FG TEXT}@{bpen 0}

@{par}For using the FreshIcons, you need a Workbench screen with 16 colors an if
possible a harddisk. Yep, this is all you need.

@{par}Some of the additional tools need at least @{"MUI" LINK "MUIInfo"} version 3.x by Stefan Stuntz.

@ENDNODE
/*E*/
/*S*/ MUI
@NODE MUIInfo "FreshIcons-Documentation / MUI-Info"
@{bpen 4}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{b}@{u}1.1 MUI-Information@{uu}@{ub}@{FG TEXT}@{bpen 0}
@{par}                          This application uses


@{par}                        MUI - MagicUserInterface

@{par}                (c) Copyright 1993-97 by Stefan Stuntz


@{par}MUI is a system to generate and maintain graphical user interfaces. With
@{par}the  aid  of  a  preferences program, the user of an application has the
@{par}ability to customize the outfit according to his personal taste.

@{par}MUI is distributed as shareware. To obtain a complete package containing
@{par}lots of examples and more information about registration please look for
@{par}a  file  called  "muiXXusr.lha"  (XX means the latest version number) on
@{par}your local bulletin boards or on public domain disks.

@{par}          If you want to register directly, feel free to send


@{par}                         DM 30.-  or  US$ 20.-

@{par}                                  to

@{par}                             Stefan Stuntz
@{par}                        Eduard-Spranger-Straße 7
@{par}                             80935 München
@{par}                                GERMANY


@ENDNODE
