/*E*/
/*S*/ Software
@NODE "Software-Hersteller" "FreshIcons-Documentation / Software-Developer"
@{b}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}
@{bpen 5}@{jcenter}@{par}@{apen 9} To all Software-Developer and (PD-)Programmers @{bpen 0}@{FG TEXT}@{ub}

@{par}If you are interested in providing icons in  FreshDesign  for
@{par}your  software  and  don't  have  the  time  or abilities for
@{par}creating your own FreshIcons just @{"contact" LINK "Adresse"} me!

@{par}Also if you  intent  to  adapt  your  program's  GUI  to  the
@{par}FreshPalette  or  to pep-up your GUI with colored symbols and
@{par}you need icons for your purposes.


@{par}@{b}@{FG FILL}@{apen 11} Further: @{FG TEXT}@{ub}
@{par}While installation of FreshIcons the program LockFreshPens is
@{par}copied  into your C: and later your user-startup ist modified
@{par}to run this program everytime you boot. This program sets the
@{par}FreshPalette  everytime  the  Workbench-Screen  is opened and
@{par}creates  a  ENV-Variable  "PALETTESET".  If   this   Variable
@{par}contains  the  value "FRESH", you can assume the FreshPalette
@{par}to be present.

@{par}So  you  can  realize  colored  hints  e.g.  @{apen 8}red@{apen 1}   errortext,
@{par}important messages in @{apen 14}yellow@{apen 1}, or @{apen 13}green@{apen 1} annotations. Even fuel
@{par}/ busy-gauges can be colored.

@{par}@{CODE}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{b}@{apen 10}Fresh-Up our AMIGA, for a colorful future!@{ub}@{FG TEXT}

@ENDNODE
